    "summary": "Professor Dr. Ben van Lier is Director Strategy & Innovation at Centric, a Dutch IT company with offices in Belgium, Norway, Sweden, Germany, Romania and Lithuania. In this capacity, he focuses on research and analyses of developments in the interface between organizations and technology. Alongside his work at Centric, in 2009 he obtained his PhD from the Rotterdam School of Management (Erasmus University). In 2013, he was appointed Professor at Steinbeis University Berlin, a role he performs alongside his work at Centric and his ongoing research into areas such as systems and complexity theory, interoperability of information, the network centric approach and information and ethics. In 2015 he was also appointed Professor at Rotterdam University of Applied Sciences in which role he does research into the emerging (Industrial) Internet of Things, blockchain technology and cybersecurity. ",
